function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return replace(lowercase(col), ' ' => '_', '\t' => '_', '\n' => '', '\r' => '')
end
```

This function takes a string `col` and returns a new string with the specified modifications. It first lowercases the column name, then strips leading and trailing whitespaces using the `replace` function along with tab characters (`'\t'`), line breaks (`'\n'`), and carriage returns (`'\r'`). Finally, it replaces spaces and hyphens with an underscore.
